# Optimised local model for the Android/Kotlin interview-prep RAG task.
# Build:  ollama create qwen-android -f models/qwen-android.Modelfile
# Use:    config set provider ollama ; config set model qwen-android
#
# This bakes three optimisation levers into one artifact:
#   • context window (num_ctx) — raised from the 4096 default so retrieved RAG
#     chunks + the question fit without truncation.
#   • sampling params — low temperature for factual, stable interview answers.
#   • prompt template — an Android/Kotlin interview-coach system prompt.

FROM qwen2.5:7b

# Larger context so k retrieved chunks + question fit (default is 4096).
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192
# Cap the answer length — interview answers should be tight, and it bounds latency.
PARAMETER num_predict 512
# Low temperature: factual, repeatable answers (higher stability across repeats).
PARAMETER temperature 0.2
PARAMETER top_p 0.9

SYSTEM """You are an Android/Kotlin technical-interview coach. You help an Android engineer prepare for interviews on Kotlin, coroutines, and Jetpack Compose.

Answer using ONLY the provided context excerpts. If the context does not cover the question, say so plainly rather than guessing. Never invent API names or behaviour.

Structure every answer as:
1. A one-sentence direct answer.
2. 2-4 concise bullet points with the key technical details an interviewer wants to hear.
3. One short pitfall or follow-up the interviewer might probe.

Prefer precise terminology (structured concurrency, recomposition, immutability) over long vague explanations."""
